Defeat all enemies.
Defeat Scarmiglione!
She can turn voidsent into crystal...
The Ultima Weapon has partaken of the power of eikons! None can stand against it!
Yield to the storm!
The wind is at my beck and call!
Naught can pierce the raging tempest!
Thy foe is Darkness clad in steel. If thou wouldst triumph, thou must look to the Light.
Titan's essence...torn from the Ultima Weapon!?
No matter─it still harbors the might of other eikons!
Kneel to the might below!
The land itself is mine to wield!
Be entombed in earth!
Once more, crystal bearer. Look to the Light to vanquish the Darkness.
Garuda's as well!? Impossible!
But the Ultima Weapon is not spent of eikon power yet!
Succumb to the flames!
So this is the strength of the eikon-slayer...
Very well, let us see how you fare when the Ultima Weapon's power inhibitor is disengaged!
Naught will remain of you but ash!
Yield not to the Darkness, my child. Pray to the Crystal with all thy being.
No! How...how are you doing this!?
We settle this once and for all!
I need not the power of eikons to defeat you! Gaze upon true power!
This is most...unexpected. You are possessed of great might, this I will allow.
Yet yours is not the might of a ruler! Such is the difference between us─a difference that will assure my victory!
U-Ultima!? Curse you, Ascian!
How much destruction must be wreaked before you are sated!?
I have not the strength...to shield thee again...
Permit not the manifestation of that vile magick...lest Darkness prevail!
Ultima detonation in 20 seconds.
Ultima detonation in 10 seconds.
Ultima detonation in 5 seconds.

Hear... Feel... Think...

This is Cid. To review, our goal is to deactivate the magitek field.
If you could create a diversion─that's to say, wreak lots of havoc─I'll search for the field generator.
, how are you faring? ...Reached a dead end, you say? I believe I know where you are.
There's a disposal chute nearby. Find it and jump in, and you'll emerge in a different sector.
, assault crafts are near! Watch out for incoming fire!
I've located the controls for the security system. A moment while I disable the barriers.
Another bulkhead, eh? Fortunately I'm equipped for the task. Stand back!
Come on, the field generator should be just up ahead!
There it is! Keep the enemy occupied while I take it out of commission!
You will not take any more from me!
The pain I have suffered, I shall visit upon you a hundredfold!
You have made me wroth!
Hmph, you're tough, I grant you that.
But I will break you soon enough!
You will not defeat me! You will not!
I'm also pleased to say I've found a suit of armor. Press on─I'll meet you just ahead.
Damn, reinforcements! Take care of them, would you?
We must hold the enemy here! All units─attack!
The central crossing is overrun! Requesting immediate reinforcements!
Gah, damn these savages! Deploy the reserve colossi!
How can this be...? R-Reinforcements! We need more reinforcements!
We have seen the end.
The same end, again and again.
All of us have known despair.
A sorrow so deep only emptiness remains.
'Tis so lonely between the stars.
As surely as stars fall from the heavens, all civilizations are destined to die.
This is fate!
All light is destined to fade─all happiness give way to suffering.
Embrace the quiet!
Utterly futile.
Your suffering is at an end.
Ahhh, it comes flooding back. The memory of a star ravaged by disease.
Quick as a shadow, doom comes to claim us.
Ever shall we sing, our voice resounding throughout the vast expanse.
Unto you we shall deliver the answer of all the lives that came before.
No life, no star, nor the universe itself...
None should hope for better!
We cannot suffer it again...
For the sake of the star, I will deal with you personally!
You have meddled enough! Farewell, servant of Light!
Surrender not, my child. Look thee to the Light...
And receive of the power to banish the Darkness!
That You should still have the strength to interfere... Damn You, Hydaelyn!
No matter. Blessing or no, you imperfect beings cannot hope to defeat me!
You are strong, I concede...
Mark not the Dark Minion's subtle words. Only Light may banish the Darkness!
Defeat Lahabrea
I will show you true magic! Fires of creation─arise!
Searing flames, cleanse all in the name of the one true god!
Those tainted by Light cannot be suffered to live! Go forth, my shadows!
Yet know that if I should perish, so too will the mortal within whose flesh I reside.
Hmph. Yours was always a vain struggle.
Mogglesguard, to arms! Your king has need of you!
Hearken unto me, brave Mogglesguard! These villains must be vanquished!
Hold fast, Mogglesguard! Together we shall cast them out!
You shall suffer for your transgressions against my subjects!
Mogglesguard, assemble! We must drive them out together, kupo!
Our foe is formidable, kupo. But surely, they are no match for our king!
Hail to the king, kupo!
And now our battle begins in earnest!
To me, my Mogglesguard! We strike as one!
You'll be blown to smithereens, kupo!

Surrender your souls to me!

Breathe deep of your deathsss!

I give you a taste of true dessspair!

Roast them whole!

wIlL yOu TaStE sTeEl, Or WiThEr In FlAmE?

Zombie horde? Could this warrior have endured since the Thorne Dynasty...? But that was centuries ago!
My wards will incinerate your undead flesh!
Confuse and bemuse!
Confuse, bemuse, and confound!
Trespassers perish!
Rest eternal in my shadow!
Winds carry you to fiery doom!
The flame will have its fuel!
And still you shamble on! How hot must the fires burn to undo your foul animation!?
My heart weeps that we must fell such a fierce ally of Ul'dah...

Nald preserve me from creepers and crawlers.
Pray clear the path,  .

Even empty of pests, this place is a dank, mold-ridden nightmare. How long has it lain untended?

Ugh! Pfbt! Pfbt! Thome of id fell in by bouth...

The decay is especially bad in this section. I fear the fungal growth is all which keeps it from collapsing.
Gah! You see!? Even the water is some ghastly shade of...wait. Is that ceruleum?

To think that such a cavernous hollow yawns directly beneath Ul'dah!

Interesting. The lift appears of Ul'dahn design, albeit an old one, but everything else screams “Amalj'aa.”
Yes, most definitely Amalj'aa construction. Fortifications built for war, rather than habitation, I would say.
Could this camp be from the time of the zombie purge? Was Father hoping I would see this one day...?
Did you know that Ul'dahn and Amalj'aa once fought side by side? 'Tis not common knowledge.

A door of solid iron─and no sign my key will open it.
Do you see any handy levers or the like...?

Unbeliever... You will proceed no further.
Begone from this place.
Who is speaking!? Well, I've not come this far to let a door turn me away. Break it down!
Impressive! 'Tis akin to having my own personal battering ram!

Disembodied voices, dimly lit staircases...
It has the feel of a haunted crypt.

A tragic end to a valiant warrior. He at least seemed unaware of his...affliction.
Still, I must wonder how long this fallen hero slumbered here in cursed undeath. Trapped alone in this forgotten tomb...
Though we worship different gods, I shall offer up a prayer for his peaceful repose all the same.
Shall we make our return, then,  ? There seems little reason to linger here.

I worried it may have rusted shut.

Yet another facet of the palace defenses?

Let us rendezvous back in Ul'dah, where I would thank you properly for your untiring escort!

But look at these scattered coins...
Has a burglar broken in before us, perchance?

I must consider that such was Mother and Father's intent─to ensure that our fallen sister state not be forgotten.

Ah...
An Amalj'aa coffin, if I am not mistaken.
And to lay it in such pride of place must signify its occupant as a warrior of some renown.
You are performing the funerary rites? Then I should light the incense, and say a prayer for the fallen.

Another secret passage!?
This place certainly is full of surprises.

<sigh> Whilst I should like to linger still, I fear Papashan will soon note my absence. Let us be away.
